Teferi’s protection is unique in that it’s a better fog stapled to a better heroic intervention type effect, but realistically you can find a dirt cheap option that mostly gets you there. I replaced it with rootborn defenses just because I wanted it for another deck, and there haven’t been many situations I’ve noticed the downgrade
I like RBD
Safe Passage is also good in a meta with lots of burn wraths
Boros charm does work too, and I’ve died to the 4 damage mode
People also forget that you can redirect that damage to walkers. Boros charm kinda has a 4th mode of remove 4 loyalty from target Planeswalker
Not for much longer.
They're patching that ruoe
Rule

Well, they’re patching it, but it seems like cards are basically just getting “...or target planeswalker” tacked onto the text.

So Charm would be deal 4 to target player or planeswalker.
Teferi’s protection works well if folks run Mindslaver or Sen Triplets decks.
Mason, in theory, though you saw all the shit they missed with the recent Dino eratta.
I don’t think they missed it, Dean. I suspect that was intentional.
Especially since there’s a second wave of Dino errata coming
I don’t think those two situations are quite comparable. There were some “misses,” yes, but there are some would-be Dinosaurs people are just reaching for.
It seemed sloppy. There were lots of creatures that were very clearly Dinosaurs, ie Regal Behemoth, which was stolen from the Ixalan design file anyway, which did not receive eratta
Errata*
I suspect that errata effort was of far lesser priority than the Planeswalker rule change
You're probably not wrong about that. I'm just saying, don't get your hopes up necessarily
I live life without hope.

Yup. Regal Behemoth is getting looked at, but I’m not surprised by it not getting changed either.

However, considering there’s a lot of disagreement here with what should and shouldn’t be changed with something as niche as Dinosaurs, I’m not excited for this errata if it’s coming. There’s just too many cards
Mason, exactly.
And how do they decide on cards that deal damage to all creatures and players like Cahndra's Ignition and Pyrohemia?
They're going to either become much more powerful, or much weaker.

If they didn’t errata Ghostly Prison to include planeswalkers when Sphere of Safety became a thing, I️ don’t feel they should errata damage effects either. There are a lot of cases that will become confusing. Just removing the rule and printing new damage effects that specifically mention whether they can hit planeswalkers sounds much cleaner to me. But they’re probably afraid of what that would do to modern and stuff, which is fair. Just gonna be messier.
